Alagi Manga is 41-years-old. He did not complete primary school and therefore has not gone to university.

When he was 18-years-old, he left school and got a job. Read his story to find out what it is like growing up and not going to school in The Gambia.

"My name is Alagi Manga. And there was somebody who asked me what happened to me, I said, ‘nothing happened to me. I decided to stay out of school from the first level to grade six. Then when I left grade six, I took up a job. Then I left and went to the military at 18 and I left and served for one year. Then I got a job in a food factory as a food packer. I worked there for five years. I received training. I can pack things and deliver them to the stores. It is just like the experience, the experience can give you the feel of doing it."

What is life like in the Gambia in 2005?
